id: pm-7n8v
title: "Drift-cache gc scope: pm gc --scope runtime should clear history-drift-cache.json"
description: The drift verification cache at .agents/pm/runtime/history-drift-cache.json is not covered by pm gc --scope runtime. The runtime scope target list in gc.ts only covers runtime/test-runs/. A stale drift cache after manual history edits can cause pm health to report false-clean results until it naturally invalidates.
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:history","area:storage",correctness,gc
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:02:16.723Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T10:15:54.087Z"
author: audit-data-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Add `{ scope: 'runtime', relativePath: 'runtime/history-drift-cache.json', kind: 'file' }` to `GC_TARGETS`\n- `pm gc --scope runtime` removes the drift cache (triggers a fresh full-scan on next `pm health`)\n- GC guidance updated to mention that removing the drift cache forces a full re-scan\n- Unit test covering the new target path"
parent: pm-o2kc
risk: low
confidence: high
body: "## Context\n\n`src/core/history/drift-scan.ts:19` writes `DRIFT_CACHE_FILENAME = 'history-drift-cache.json'` to `runtime/`. The gc runtime scope target at `src/cli/commands/gc.ts:41-48` only includes `runtime/test-runs`.\n\nIf an operator manually edits a history JSONL file (e.g. to repair after an external tool), the mtime/ctime/size/content-hash in the drift cache will be stale. The health scan will re-verify on content-hash mismatch, but `pm gc --scope runtime` fails to purge the cache as expected.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add `{ scope: 'runtime', relativePath: 'runtime/history-drift-cache.json', kind: 'file' }` to `GC_TARGETS`\n- [ ] `pm gc --scope runtime` removes the drift cache (triggers a fresh full-scan on next `pm health`)\n- [ ] GC guidance updated to mention that removing the drift cache forces a full re-scan\n- [ ] Unit test covering the new target path\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `src/cli/commands/gc.ts:41-48` — `runtime` GC_TARGET only covers `runtime/test-runs`\n- `src/core/history/drift-scan.ts:19` — cache path is `runtime/history-drift-cache.json`\n- `src/core/history/drift-scan.ts:36-49` — `loadDriftCache` reads from this path"
